{"lemma":"وَلِيَ","slug":"وَلِيَ","root":"ل","root_slug":"ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ل","pos":"PREP","pos_camel":"prep","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَلِيَ","root":"ولي","pos":"V","occurrence_count":30},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["character","conj","particle","prep","symbol","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n44745","n44750"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"character","gloss":"The twenty-third letter of the Arabic alphabet, written in the Arabic script; preceded by ك (k) and followed by م (m).","tags":["letter"]},{"pos":"symbol","gloss":"The twelfth numeral symbol of the Arabic alphabet (traditional abjad order, used for list numbering), written in the Arabic script; preceded by ك (k) and followed by م (m)."},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"to, for, belonging to","examples":[{"text":"تَيَسَّرَ لِلسَّفَرِ","english":"Travel became easy."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"Used to express admiration","examples":[{"text":"يَا لَلْعَجَبِ!","english":"How wonderful!"},{"text":"يَا لَهُ مِنْ عَالَمٍ رَائِعٍ!","english":"What a wonderful world!"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"Used to call for help","examples":[{"text":"يَا لَلْأُمِّ لِلْأَطْفَالِ!","english":"Oh for mother to the children! (Oh mother, help your children!)"}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"to, in order to: followed by the subjunctive mood","examples":[{"text":"دَخَلْتُ ٱلْمَطْبَخَ لِأَشْرَبَ مَاءً.","english":"I entered the kitchen to drink water."}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"used with the verbs أَرَادَ (ʔarāda) and أَمَرَ (ʔamara)","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّمَا يُرِيدُ اللّٰهُ لِيُذْهِبَ عَنْكُمُ الرِّجْسَ","english":"Allah only intends to purify you of impurity."}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"only to (لَامُ الْعَاقِبَة (lāmu l-ʕāqiba))","examples":[{"text":"فَالْتَقَطَهُ آلُ فِرْعَوْنَ لِيَكُونَ لَهُمْ عَدُوًّا وَحَزَنًا","english":"And so the family of the Pharaoh picked him up, only to become an enemy and a grief."}]},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"Used to introduce an imperative with a jussive verb; let","examples":[{"text":"لِتَأْخُذُوا مَنَاسِكَكُمْ فَإِنِّي لَا أَدْرِي لَعَلِّي لَا أَحُجُّ بَعْدَ حَجَّتِي هَذِهِ","english":"Learn your rituals from me, for I do not know—perhaps this will be my last Hajj."},{"text":"وَقُلِ ٱلْحَقُّ مِنْ رَبِّكُمْ فَمَنْ شَاءَ فَلْيُؤْمِنْ وَمَنْ شَاءَ فَلْيَكْفُرْ","english":"And say, \"The truth is from your Lord, so whoever wills, let him believe; and whoever wills, let him disbelieve.\""}]},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"truly, verily, certainly, surely","examples":[{"text":"وَإِنَّ أَوْهَنَ ٱلْبُيُوتِ لَبَيْتُ ٱلْعَنْكَبُوتِ","english":"And indeed, the weakest of homes is the home of the spider."},{"text":"إِنَّ رَبَّكَ لَبِالْمِرْصَادِ","english":"Verily, thy Lord is on the lookout."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the Nabataean Aramaic letter 𐢑 (l, “lāmaḏ”), derived from the Phoenician letter 𐤋 (l, “lāməd”), from the Egyptian hieroglyph 𓌅. See also Classical Syriac ܠ (l, “lāmaḏ”), Hebrew ל (l, “lamed”), Ancient Greek Λ (L), Greek Λ (L), Latin L.\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *lV-."},"ipa":["/laːm/","/l/","/ɫ/","/li./","/la./"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44745","headword_ar":"وَلَّى","root":"wlY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He caused to turn away, or back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kur-án, ch. ii. v. 136.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He caused to turn towards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with acc. (Idem, ch. ii. v. 139.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY Eanohu","text_ar":"وَلَّى عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned away from, avoided, shunned, and left, him or it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~ati AlHarobu","text_ar":"وَلَّتِ الحَرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The war declined"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sfr","text_ar":"سفر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY haAribFA","text_ar":"وَلَّى هَارِبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retreated, fleeing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~ayotuhu ZahoriY","text_ar":"وَلَّيْتُهُ ظَهْرِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I placed him behind me, and betook myself to defending him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$zn","text_ar":"شزن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  More commonly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I turned my back upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see Har, p. 564. ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY All~ayolu liya*ohaba","text_ar":"وَلَّى اللَّيْلُ لِيَذْهَبَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retreated to depart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adobara","text_ar":"اَدْبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY A^amoru Alqawomi lifasaAdi","text_ar":"وَلَّى اَمْرُ القَوْمِ لِفَسَادِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The case of the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became reduced to a bad state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adobara","text_ar":"اَدْبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b11-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY kibarFA","text_ar":"وَلَّى كِبَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY","text_ar":"وَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, both of frequent occurrence in the lexicons, &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became in a declining state by reason of age."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY","text_ar":"وَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabara","text_ar":"دَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ay~axa","text_ar":"شَيَّخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See also two exs., p. 75, col. 3. ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~awoliyapu","text_ar":"التَّوْلِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_idobaAru","text_ar":"الاـِدْبَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Retrogression;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, like this English word, tropically,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declension."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aAhu A^amorFA","text_ar":"وَلَّاهُ اَمْرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set him over the thing; appointed him superintendent of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set him to do it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAhu","text_ar":"اَوْلَاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY duburahu","text_ar":"وَلَّى دُبُرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aAhu duburahu","text_ar":"وَلَّاهُ دُبُرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duburN","text_ar":"دُبُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and see three phrases voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*anabN","text_ar":"ذَنَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n44750","headword_ar":"وَلِىٌّ","root":"wlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manager of a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of another: (Msb:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guardian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manager of the affairs, and maintainer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an orphan: the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guardian"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a women,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who affiances"},{"kind":"text","text":"her,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and independently of whom marriage cannot be contracted"},{"kind":"text","text":"by her. (TA.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"executor"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a deceased person: (Bd, xvii. 35:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heir"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a deceased person. (Bd, Jel, ibid.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next-of-kin"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a slain person, (Bd, Jel, xvii. 35,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has the management of the affairs after the death"},{"kind":"text","text":"of that person. (Bd, ibid.) And the slayer's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next-of-kin, who is answerable for him."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~u EahodK","text_ar":"وَلِىُّ عَهْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wilaAyapu EahodK","text_ar":"وِلَايَةُ عَهْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ehd","text_ar":"عهد"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~ A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"وَلِىّ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The friend of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~N","text_ar":"وَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the meaning of an act. part. n., i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant obeyer"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of God]: or that of a pass. part. n., i. e. [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favourite"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God;] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of the constant beneficence and favours"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God. (TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~N","text_ar":"عَدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^all~`hu waliY~u AlHamodi","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ وَلِىُّ الحَمْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaHiq~uhu","text_ar":"مُسْتَحِقُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibuhu","text_ar":"صَاحِبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IbrD.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~N","text_ar":"وَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoliyaA'u","text_ar":"اَوْلِيَاءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A saint, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~N","text_ar":"وَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasomiY~","text_ar":"وَسْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Enw","text_ar":"عنو"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":3061}],"source_refs":["Msb"]}]}}